1
00:00:00,530 --> 00:00:01,520
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,550 --> 00:00:02,550
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:18,560
[Love Upon a Time Series]

4
00:00:18,650 --> 00:00:22,560
Grant me your forgiveness,
I beg of you, Klao.

5
00:00:32,210 --> 00:00:33,360
So...

6
00:00:33,680 --> 00:00:34,840
Which temple is it?

7
00:00:36,080 --> 00:00:37,970
It is Wat Sema Muang.

8
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:57,070
My father brought me to that temple as a child.

9
00:00:57,490 --> 00:00:59,160
Is it true that the meeting place

10
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,800
lies in the woods behind it,

11
00:01:02,220 --> 00:01:03,060
Pim?

12
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:07,880
Indeed, on the second period of
the fifteenth night of the waning moon,

13
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:15,720
the opium trade shall occur
at the hut by the river every month.

14
00:01:20,860 --> 00:01:25,240
Klao, are you certain that
you shall not inform the patrolmen?

15
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,720
I must witness it with my own eyes.

16
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:33,320
To report it to them without certainty

17
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:36,450
may serve only to tarnish
both Phop's name and my own.

18
00:01:57,270 --> 00:01:59,140
Are you courting death?

19
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:21,960
Where the devil is he?!

20
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:40,050
Klao!

21
00:02:40,380 --> 00:02:41,400
Show yourself!

22
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:44,120
Find him,
or you shall not live to see the dawn!

23
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:44,950
Everyone...

24
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,680
Move!

25
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:11,000
Goodness!

26
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:12,640
Whither do you think to escape me?!!

27
00:03:31,930 --> 00:03:34,100
You are far more stubborn than your father.

28
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,520
I seek no quarrel with you.

29
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:41,960
But you!

30
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:45,600
You refuse to let us be.

31
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:48,470
Your meddling has at last
exhausted his patience.

32
00:03:48,490 --> 00:03:51,520
He has ordered me
to send you to hell to join your father.

33
00:03:56,650 --> 00:03:57,600
If this is my end,

34
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:02,240
then I shall drag you all,
you scum of the earth,

35
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:03,740
down into hell with me.

36
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:27,130
Go and mark me a place
in the depths of hell, then!!

37
00:04:27,230 --> 00:04:27,880
Klao!!

38
00:04:42,159 --> 00:04:43,310
Unless...

39
00:04:44,550 --> 00:04:46,680
you change your mind and join us.

40
00:04:48,490 --> 00:04:50,490
The opium trade flows with gold.

41
00:04:51,990 --> 00:04:53,680
One may make a fortune overnight.

42
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:58,260
If you serve as our informer,

43
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,630
feeding us news,

44
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,640
the words of your superiors,

45
00:05:03,450 --> 00:05:06,390
and every move your brother
Lord Phop makes,

46
00:05:07,130 --> 00:05:09,040
you may be handsomely rewarded.

47
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:13,800
What say you, Klao?

48
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:17,540
If you are wise, accept the offer,

49
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:20,440
and I shall spare your life.

50
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:33,200
Not in this life.

51
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:13,240
You are just as stubborn as ever.

52
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:20,400
Pim,

53
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,800
why must you do this to me?

54
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,650
For a mere handful of coins,

55
00:06:41,350 --> 00:06:43,500
you chose to stoop this low?

56
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:47,200
I only wish to redeem myself
and live a life far from the capital.

57
00:06:49,390 --> 00:06:52,250
What more could a woman
such as I ever hope for?

58
00:06:55,150 --> 00:06:56,200
Back then,

59
00:06:57,030 --> 00:07:00,250
I truly hoped you would capture Cherd,

60
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:03,140
so that he would no longer be in my life.

61
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,520
When you failed,

62
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:09,600
I was truly devastated,
and that remains so.

63
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,500
But now

64
00:07:17,430 --> 00:07:19,450
you have uncovered too much,

65
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,490
and I fear I am the one in danger.

66
00:07:24,530 --> 00:07:25,720
Cease this, Pim.

67
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:27,160
Kla,

68
00:07:28,660 --> 00:07:30,450
leave at once before anyone finds you.

69
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:36,200
What of the promise

70
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:39,400
- to grant me the title of lord?
- Begone, I say!!

71
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:45,140
He shall see to it
once you reach Pak Nam Pho.

72
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,060
I have the vessel ready behind the hut.

73
00:07:49,090 --> 00:07:51,360
Begone at once.

74
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:54,250
As you wish.

75
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,760
Grant me your forgiveness, Master Klao.

76
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:14,980
Wait!

77
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:16,280
Pim!

78
00:08:17,290 --> 00:08:18,840
There is no way out to the river!

79
00:08:19,030 --> 00:08:20,640
It is but a pond. It leads nowhere!

80
00:08:21,030 --> 00:08:22,320
What? What are you doing?!

81
00:08:31,670 --> 00:08:33,919
Such is the nature of this world, Klao.

82
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,200
[Love Upon a Time Series]

83
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:59,840
[Love Upon a Time Series]

84
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,430
When I returned,

85
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:10,170
I prayed that you had lost
your memory forever, as the rumors had it.

86
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:13,360
Yet you remain as stubborn as a mule,

87
00:10:14,690 --> 00:10:17,230
digging into the past
until you have recalled everything.

88
00:10:18,090 --> 00:10:19,360
Klao, I truly wish to know

89
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,390
how on earth you managed to return
from the brink of death.

90
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:24,230
I saw my men

91
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:27,120
throw you into the pond with my own eyes.

92
00:10:28,490 --> 00:10:31,170
And I shall do the very same

93
00:10:31,220 --> 00:10:33,000
to Pim and Kla.

94
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:41,080
Klao,

95
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:46,510
are you some kind of spirit?
What unholy power do you possess? Huh?!

96
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:48,660
Answer me!

97
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,570
Finish me off once again at this instant,

98
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:57,320
before Phop comes to save me.

99
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,360
Your foolishness remains unchanged.

100
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:19,970
I never took your life, Klao.

101
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:43,120
What did he say?

102
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:45,720
He refused.

103
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:32,700
You have left me no choice in this, Klao.

104
00:12:35,530 --> 00:12:37,030
You claim this meddling

105
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:41,550
is for your father's sake,

106
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,740
but I too do this for my father.

107
00:13:07,530 --> 00:13:10,130
Bid the world farewell, Klao.

108
00:13:32,470 --> 00:13:33,310
Cherd.

109
00:13:33,860 --> 00:13:34,860
Yes, my Lord...

110
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:39,830
Send him to his grave.

111
00:13:41,110 --> 00:13:41,950
Yes, my Lord.

112
00:14:04,070 --> 00:14:06,200
Lord Harn was the one who dealt the blow.

113
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,080
I merely cleaned up his mess.

114
00:14:10,010 --> 00:14:13,440
But tonight, I shall send you
to your watery grave by my own hand.

115
00:14:13,670 --> 00:14:14,840
How does that sound, Klao?

116
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:17,040
Agonizing, is it not?

117
00:14:21,950 --> 00:14:23,340
Fear not

118
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,450
that you will be alone in hell,

119
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:30,560
for your good brother

120
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:33,520
shall soon join you.

121
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:36,720
No...

122
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:42,170
You two shall be in hell together tonight.

123
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:43,780
Splendid, is it not?

124
00:14:44,060 --> 00:14:44,820
Wonderful, is it not?

125
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,800
Is this not wonderful?!

126
00:14:50,730 --> 00:14:51,830
Make haste!!

127
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:52,680
At once!!

128
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:05,200
Lay down your sword.

129
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:10,640
Lay down your sword, I say!

130
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:23,560
Patrolmen...

131
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,800
You were so near to escaping your fate, Phop.

132
00:15:37,350 --> 00:15:39,360
Had you wed Lady Varna,

133
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:42,460
we would have been part of the same family,

134
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:45,120
allowing me to keep a closer eye on you.

135
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:48,620
We would not have come to this.

136
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:00,360
When did I give you away?

137
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:03,200
Was it the absence of a pond here?

138
00:16:04,060 --> 00:16:05,640
I saw right through you long ago.

139
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:09,140
Every time we close in
on those opium traffickers,

140
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,160
they still manage to slip through our fingers.

141
00:16:13,560 --> 00:16:15,860
And when it comes time for interrogation,

142
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:18,800
none are willing to confess.

143
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,930
The soldiers have captured the smugglers

144
00:16:20,970 --> 00:16:23,680
who carried opium
from the capital to sell in Sam Khok.

145
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:26,120
My father conducted the interrogation himself,

146
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,440
yet none of them would confess.

147
00:16:28,730 --> 00:16:31,040
Who would dare to implicate their own master,

148
00:16:31,870 --> 00:16:33,200
and do so to his face?

149
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:39,910
But what clearly gave you away

150
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:42,750
was the poisoning of the patrolmen.

151
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:47,640
To make them lower their guard
and become intoxicated

152
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,320
would require an insider.

153
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,360
It smells of burnt beans.

154
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:54,020
Are they castor beans?

155
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:57,140
These people have been poisoned.

156
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:03,260
And there is also Kla.

157
00:17:04,069 --> 00:17:07,119
Unless it was someone of
equal rank to mine or higher,

158
00:17:09,089 --> 00:17:11,800
there was no way he could have been bought
as an informant.

159
00:17:15,839 --> 00:17:18,480
Every trail leads back to you and your father.

160
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:24,200
You are far too clever for your own good.

161
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:26,680
But if you are truly so bright,

162
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,440
why did you follow me here?

163
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:32,520
Merely to buy time.

164
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:39,840
By now, your father
has surely been captured by my father's men.

165
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,720
High Lord Pichayabhakdi.

166
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:55,240
By what means did you find out...

167
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:57,160
that it was I?

168
00:17:58,540 --> 00:17:59,720
The document.

169
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:03,800
It bears Lord Preechapiban's name,

170
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
with a smear of ink
running from left to right.

171
00:18:08,050 --> 00:18:10,030
The handwriting is indeed identical
in every respect.

172
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:13,380
Yet my father never smudged ink
upon his writings.

173
00:18:14,210 --> 00:18:16,650
Why, then, is there an ink blot here
and nowhere else?

174
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,140
Hence, the forger

175
00:18:22,380 --> 00:18:24,130
must be...

176
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,350
left-handed.

177
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,130
High Lord.

178
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:34,760
We are officials of the state,

179
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:38,210
entrusted with the duty
of safeguarding the welfare of the people.

180
00:18:38,670 --> 00:18:39,960
Having been granted a life

181
00:18:40,170 --> 00:18:42,360
far more bountiful
than that of the common folk,

182
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,560
we cannot commit such an act.

183
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,880
Pray, accept it.

184
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:57,680
I merely need you to act as my intermediary
with the Farangi and the Chinese.

185
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:01,460
Nothing will ever be traced back to you.
You have my assurance.

186
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,600
I shall accept only your kindness.

187
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:12,860
As for all else,

188
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,260
I must most respectfully decline.

189
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:22,000
Should any word of opium smuggling
reach me from the capital,

190
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:24,080
I fear...

191
00:19:25,110 --> 00:19:27,180
you shall be the first...

192
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:29,880
I suspect.

193
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:38,140
Be that as it may,

194
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:43,860
remain here
and wallow in your misery in Phichit.

195
00:19:45,870 --> 00:19:47,130
Lord Preechapiban

196
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:49,960
was a man of many talents,

197
00:19:50,650 --> 00:19:52,230
yet he was a fool.

198
00:19:54,950 --> 00:19:56,080
The moment...

199
00:19:56,730 --> 00:19:59,520
I summoned him to the capital in your name,

200
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:01,800
he recklessly came,

201
00:20:02,830 --> 00:20:05,160
believing he could lend you his aid.

202
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:07,540
That trickery

203
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:10,680
presented me with the perfect opportunity

204
00:20:11,370 --> 00:20:13,420
to steal his personal seal

205
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:16,320
and forge the document.

206
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:24,950
High Lord.

207
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,240
High Lord...

208
00:20:46,140 --> 00:20:47,320
How pitiful.

209
00:20:51,840 --> 00:20:52,930
It is a shame

210
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:58,640
that you are
just as foolish as your dearest friend.

211
00:20:59,410 --> 00:21:01,090
You shall never know,

212
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,320
not even in the slightest,

213
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:04,560
that Meng and I

214
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:07,740
conspired to poison your tea.

215
00:21:12,490 --> 00:21:13,680
With this settled,

216
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,840
Lord Preechapiban's secret

217
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:21,030
shall go to the grave with you.

218
00:21:22,550 --> 00:21:23,400
Your Excellency,

219
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:24,720
an opium shipment list

220
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:26,880
has been discovered
concealed beneath his manor.

221
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:27,880
Huh...

222
00:21:37,710 --> 00:21:39,950
So, you lured me out to lead me into a trap,

223
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:40,930
High Lord?!

224
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,320
Precisely.

225
00:21:43,890 --> 00:21:44,760
Now then,

226
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:46,120
who is the fool

227
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:50,000
at this hour, High Lord?!

228
00:21:57,870 --> 00:21:59,340
So, Meng

229
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:03,390
has chosen to turn against me?

230
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,530
Meng

231
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,430
simply chose to stand
only on the side of justice.

232
00:22:11,230 --> 00:22:13,040
Phop visits this teahouse frequently.

233
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:14,620
Meng...

234
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,440
would never dare poison me.

235
00:22:21,150 --> 00:22:22,000
It is not over.

236
00:22:22,570 --> 00:22:25,030
Though you may have eluded my poison,

237
00:22:26,130 --> 00:22:29,120
my men are already upon you.

238
00:22:29,370 --> 00:22:30,220
Soldiers!

239
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:34,990
Lay waste to High Lord Pichayabhakdi at once!

240
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:38,240
Soldiers!

241
00:22:39,570 --> 00:22:40,420
Soldiers!!

242
00:23:02,870 --> 00:23:04,290
Accept your fate, High Lord.

243
00:23:05,430 --> 00:23:08,560
To resist or flee
would only bring you further disgrace.

244
00:23:09,550 --> 00:23:10,380
This way.

245
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:30,800
Any news of Lord Phop?

246
00:23:31,870 --> 00:23:33,360
He has yet to arrive and join us.

247
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:34,840
However, we have already

248
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:36,920
dispatched reinforcements to assist him.

249
00:24:11,140 --> 00:24:12,560
Surrender now, Phop!!

250
00:24:12,930 --> 00:24:14,200
You shall not escape this night!!

251
00:24:32,780 --> 00:24:34,080
You have been defeated, Lord Harn.

252
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:36,640
The cell awaits.

253
00:24:37,390 --> 00:24:38,920
Then you shall fall with me!!

254
00:24:39,650 --> 00:24:40,840
By now, Klao...

255
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,720
has certainly been slaughtered by Cherd.

256
00:24:45,580 --> 00:24:48,020
You did inquire about Klao's
whereabouts this evening, did you not?

257
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:50,240
Then hear me well!

258
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:54,360
Cherd conspired with Pim,
the lady of the House of Pleasure.

259
00:24:55,010 --> 00:24:56,840
He was hiding in the Pavilion of Affection

260
00:24:58,150 --> 00:24:59,720
to ensnare Klao.

261
00:25:00,510 --> 00:25:03,160
He must surely be in Cherd's hands by now.

262
00:25:07,910 --> 00:25:08,960
At last,

263
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:12,080
Klao had once again been slain,

264
00:25:14,100 --> 00:25:16,920
despite my having already killed him
with my own hands.

265
00:25:29,970 --> 00:25:31,220
Seize that Harn at once!

266
00:25:31,250 --> 00:25:32,320
I shall make my way to save Klao!

267
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:33,000
Yes, my Lord!

268
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:57,530
♫Wat Bot, oh, the temple of old,♫

269
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:02,650
♫Where seven toddy palms stand tall as told♫

270
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:09,040
♫Khun Thong went forth on the raid♫

271
00:26:11,930 --> 00:26:14,680
♫Still, he has yet to return
for the sweet embrace♫

272
00:26:18,590 --> 00:26:21,500
♫Wrapping food in a bundle,♫

273
00:26:22,710 --> 00:26:25,160
♫I rowed out to look for my angel♫

274
00:26:27,530 --> 00:26:29,610
♫Yet the rumors had already spread♫

275
00:26:31,220 --> 00:26:32,730
♫That Khun Thong had met♫

276
00:26:33,910 --> 00:26:35,020
♫His fate♫

277
00:27:01,740 --> 00:27:02,740
It is time.

278
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:05,430
Let us enjoy sending Klao
to his watery grave.

279
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,000
Still here, are you not, Cherd?

280
00:27:09,110 --> 00:27:10,830
My Lord. Oh, my Lord.

281
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:11,880
I shall depart at once.

282
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:14,190
This time, he shall certainly meet his end.

283
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:27,090
Hey! Unhand me!

284
00:27:27,130 --> 00:27:27,950
Unhand me at once!

285
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:29,050
You scoundrel!

286
00:27:29,210 --> 00:27:30,160
Cherd.

287
00:27:30,660 --> 00:27:32,200
Cherd, Cherd!

288
00:27:32,310 --> 00:27:33,120
Cherd!

289
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:39,000
Klao...

290
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:41,800
Klao...

291
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:44,520
Klao.

292
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,280
Klao.

293
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:51,850
Klao.

294
00:27:52,850 --> 00:27:53,720
Klao.

295
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,920
My deepest thanks to you,

296
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:58,380
Kaew

297
00:27:59,350 --> 00:28:00,350
and Jom.

298
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:03,420
You are in good hands now, Klao.

299
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:33,360
And...

300
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:35,400
Cherd's men...

301
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:36,750
They...

302
00:28:37,970 --> 00:28:38,970
cast

303
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:41,760
Pim and Kla into the pond.

304
00:28:52,660 --> 00:28:53,500
Jom!

305
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:54,680
Blood...

306
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,580
It is Cherd's.

307
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:13,770
You have my heartfelt thanks,

308
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:16,610
my dearest Kaew.

309
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:38,480
Rise.

310
00:29:39,370 --> 00:29:40,400
I am guiltless!

311
00:29:42,210 --> 00:29:43,120
I am innocent!!

312
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:44,740
Have you gone mad?!

313
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,840
I am merely protecting my master!

314
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:48,400
It was he who meddled with us!

315
00:29:49,630 --> 00:29:50,880
You!!

316
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:53,560
Damn you, Klao! You are the cause of this!

317
00:29:53,810 --> 00:29:56,200
I shall drag you into the depths of hell!!

318
00:29:57,950 --> 00:29:59,530
Cease this blaming at once, Cherd!

319
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,490
You are a wretched opium smoker
and a peddler.

320
00:30:04,810 --> 00:30:06,760
You attempted to murder Klao
to bury the truth.

321
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:11,010
You took Pim's life
solely to save your own skin.

322
00:30:12,910 --> 00:30:14,530
Your stupidity matches your malice.

323
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:17,150
No one is to blame for your actions.

324
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,390
I ended Pim's life...

325
00:30:35,860 --> 00:30:37,040
I killed her.

326
00:30:37,270 --> 00:30:38,720
Pim, forgive me.

327
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:43,270
I killed her.

328
00:30:43,290 --> 00:30:44,320
I killed her...

329
00:30:47,210 --> 00:30:48,830
I murdered her!

330
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:57,490
I am sorry, Pim. Forgive me.

331
00:30:57,610 --> 00:30:58,320
Take him away.

332
00:30:59,630 --> 00:31:00,440
Yes, my Lord.

333
00:31:07,130 --> 00:31:08,480
Pim, I am sorry.

334
00:31:17,650 --> 00:31:18,840
Are you injured at all?

335
00:32:26,330 --> 00:32:27,840
Toast!

336
00:32:37,710 --> 00:32:39,330
My deepest thanks to you all.

337
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:42,140
Without you,

338
00:32:43,510 --> 00:32:44,580
I would not have survived.

339
00:32:51,550 --> 00:32:52,360
By the way...

340
00:32:53,470 --> 00:32:54,820
Jom and Kaew,

341
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:56,720
how did you find me there?

342
00:32:58,320 --> 00:32:59,600
We owe our sincere thanks...

343
00:33:06,710 --> 00:33:07,480
to that young man.

344
00:33:11,530 --> 00:33:13,000
That spacing was a crime in itself.

345
00:33:15,250 --> 00:33:17,050
I told Physician Jom that

346
00:33:17,260 --> 00:33:19,400
I saw a patrolman named Kla

347
00:33:19,890 --> 00:33:22,520
linger outside the tavern every night,

348
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:25,440
speaking with Cherd in secret
once it was closed.

349
00:33:25,890 --> 00:33:26,950
They were acquainted.

350
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:29,600
That was why they helped Cherd
conceal the truth about his wound.

351
00:33:30,070 --> 00:33:32,470
Furthermore,
I crossed paths with him this evening

352
00:33:32,620 --> 00:33:34,160
on his way to the Pavilion of Affection.

353
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:35,520
Cherd

354
00:33:35,740 --> 00:33:37,200
harbors deep hatred towards Master Klao.

355
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,800
This means that

356
00:33:39,370 --> 00:33:41,200
Kla was acquainted with Cherd,

357
00:33:42,010 --> 00:33:43,540
and I feared that...

358
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:46,620
the two might conspire

359
00:33:46,790 --> 00:33:48,400
to ambush you

360
00:33:48,470 --> 00:33:50,000
once you reached the Pavilion of Affection.

361
00:33:52,590 --> 00:33:54,080
Your subordinate

362
00:33:54,690 --> 00:33:56,320
is quite eloquent, is he not?

363
00:33:56,850 --> 00:33:58,300
On this night,

364
00:33:58,890 --> 00:34:02,600
he has spoken more in a single day
than in all his life before it.

365
00:34:06,620 --> 00:34:08,420
What happened next, Jom?

366
00:34:10,469 --> 00:34:11,840
I saw Cherd here

367
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:13,580
with a certain patrolman.

368
00:34:13,820 --> 00:34:16,440
I seem to recall him being a man
under Lord Phop's command.

369
00:34:20,730 --> 00:34:21,840
This means...

370
00:34:21,860 --> 00:34:23,000
there is a traitor among Phop's men.

371
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:26,600
Kaew, summon the patrols here at once.

372
00:34:27,350 --> 00:34:28,620
Should anything occur,

373
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:30,120
they shall aid all of us.

374
00:34:33,630 --> 00:34:34,840
I cannot do this.

375
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:40,290
I place full trust in you.

376
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:44,360
Never have I known a soul
so wise and resilient as you.

377
00:35:01,950 --> 00:35:03,720
You are capable of this, Kaew.

378
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:08,360
We shall not let anything happen to Klao.

379
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:31,520
Kaew, the patrolmen, and I
kept close watch.

380
00:35:31,950 --> 00:35:33,790
But then Kla
left the establishment with a bag.

381
00:35:33,820 --> 00:35:35,380
He left alongside Pim.

382
00:35:35,970 --> 00:35:37,530
Therefore, we tracked them down to the hut.

383
00:35:39,940 --> 00:35:41,240
Unfortunately,

384
00:35:41,470 --> 00:35:43,170
the route was unknown to us,

385
00:35:44,130 --> 00:35:46,480
and so we were unable to reach
Pim and Kla in time to save them.

386
00:35:47,670 --> 00:35:50,240
I am already more than grateful
for your assistance in this.

387
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:53,120
Cherd has now been imprisoned.

388
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:56,500
Lord Harn is being hunted by my men.

389
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:58,870
He will not get far.

390
00:36:01,870 --> 00:36:03,870
The truth has come to light,

391
00:36:07,850 --> 00:36:09,240
yet one thing remains unclear.

392
00:36:10,530 --> 00:36:11,600
By what means

393
00:36:11,740 --> 00:36:15,280
did you triumph over the High Lord's men?

394
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:23,000
Master.

395
00:36:25,730 --> 00:36:26,900
A-Chai, step back.

396
00:36:26,930 --> 00:36:28,000
Retreat for but a moment.

397
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:30,120
Calm yourselves, fellow soldiers.

398
00:36:30,260 --> 00:36:32,040
No need for such haste.

399
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:34,800
Would you like some tea?
We have a kettle full here.

400
00:36:35,740 --> 00:36:37,480
After taking a sip,

401
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:40,600
you are free to cut off my head,
should that be your wish.

402
00:36:40,940 --> 00:36:43,260
Behold, in this kettle is Da Hong Pao.

403
00:36:43,290 --> 00:36:44,520
It rejuvenates your soul.

404
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:47,080
It is the very tea favored by
the current Emperor himself.

405
00:36:47,430 --> 00:36:49,760
It calms your soul

406
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:51,640
as if a bodhisattva's chant

407
00:36:51,660 --> 00:36:54,360
were echoing within your heart.

408
00:36:56,920 --> 00:37:00,000
!@#$%^&*

409
00:37:00,210 --> 00:37:01,200
!@#$%^&*

410
00:37:02,870 --> 00:37:03,600
Hey!

411
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:08,880
One.

412
00:37:09,250 --> 00:37:10,110
- Two.
- Two.

413
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:10,960
- Three.
- Three.

414
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:11,880
- Enjoy!
- Enjoy!

415
00:37:20,240 --> 00:37:21,640
Form a circle.

416
00:37:21,730 --> 00:37:22,540
Circling

417
00:37:22,580 --> 00:37:24,720
until they lose their senses.

418
00:37:24,970 --> 00:37:26,420
Circling around.

419
00:37:26,450 --> 00:37:27,840
Around and around.

420
00:37:38,180 --> 00:37:39,240
Curse you...

421
00:37:44,290 --> 00:37:45,560
His Excellency

422
00:37:45,820 --> 00:37:49,000
still draws breath tonight
because of my hand.

423
00:37:49,570 --> 00:37:51,260
Before calling the tavern my new home,

424
00:37:51,290 --> 00:37:55,840
I served as a patrolman myself.

425
00:37:57,430 --> 00:37:58,160
Not true.

426
00:37:59,760 --> 00:38:02,320
I shall lie when pigs fly.

427
00:38:02,500 --> 00:38:05,120
Go and smell its arse,
should you not believe me.

428
00:38:05,460 --> 00:38:07,360
Cease this folly, will you?

429
00:38:08,310 --> 00:38:10,570
During my days in China,

430
00:38:10,740 --> 00:38:13,690
I was placed under the tutelage
of a senior kinsman to master the martial arts.

431
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:17,440
He was my uncle's older brother,
and my uncle was my father's younger brother.

432
00:38:17,540 --> 00:38:19,250
And this man was my father's father.

433
00:38:19,290 --> 00:38:21,890
- I do not believe it in the least.
- He instructed me in the Chinese martial arts...

434
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:24,210
- Hey! What I have said is true.
- I could never believe you.

435
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:26,130
A true story, I say.

436
00:38:26,160 --> 00:38:27,370
A lie, I say.

437
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:28,430
If it was...

438
00:38:28,740 --> 00:38:30,520
- Now, now, Master.
- What of it?

439
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:32,510
You pushed me, did you not?

440
00:38:32,580 --> 00:38:35,000
- You pushed me?
- And what of it?

441
00:38:35,120 --> 00:38:36,600
You seek a challenge, do you not?

442
00:38:36,630 --> 00:38:38,160
And what of it, I ask?

443
00:38:38,270 --> 00:38:39,160
- Huh?
- Do you wish to...

444
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:41,480
- What of it?
- Ah, you have struck me.

445
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:43,060
Begone.

446
00:38:43,100 --> 00:38:45,280
- Begone, I said.
- Did you lay your hand upon me?

447
00:38:45,700 --> 00:38:46,880
Did I?

448
00:38:56,950 --> 00:38:59,240
They spun a grand tale, did they not?

449
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:01,120
In truth, they were but cowering in fear,

450
00:39:01,370 --> 00:39:03,850
leaving the men of High Lord Pichayabhakdi

451
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:06,600
to deal with those of High Lord Horathibodi.

452
00:39:09,690 --> 00:39:10,890
Unhand me.

453
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:13,190
- Let go. I must...
- Come.

454
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:14,580
Come here.

455
00:39:14,630 --> 00:39:15,890
- This way.
- Come this way.

456
00:39:15,930 --> 00:39:18,390
- A man like me does not...
- I am not afraid of you.

457
00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:20,980
Let that be known. Come this way.

458
00:39:24,130 --> 00:39:25,920
Do you truly believe their words, Klao?

459
00:39:30,430 --> 00:39:32,200
Not even in the slightest from the beginning.

460
00:39:34,820 --> 00:39:36,120
But if you ask

461
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:38,880
what I have gained from this mess,

462
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:41,540
it would be that...

463
00:39:43,260 --> 00:39:45,480
I should never again place
easy trust in the tales of others,

464
00:39:46,650 --> 00:39:47,600
perhaps.

465
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:51,810
This includes the words spun by

466
00:39:52,510 --> 00:39:55,440
others concerning my past,

467
00:39:57,070 --> 00:39:58,420
the stories of Pim,

468
00:39:59,340 --> 00:40:00,160
of Cherd,

469
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,000
of Lord Harn,

470
00:40:04,590 --> 00:40:06,120
and even those set down in the histories.

471
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:09,920
Whoever tells their stories

472
00:40:11,190 --> 00:40:13,310
shall ever seek
to paint themselves in a favorable light.

473
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,760
All has come to an end.

474
00:40:22,570 --> 00:40:24,350
If Lord Harn is brought to justice,

475
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:28,420
then your mission is undoubtedly fulfilled.

476
00:40:32,260 --> 00:40:34,160
If my mission is fulfilled,

477
00:40:38,170 --> 00:40:39,960
it means I must return to the present.

478
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:11,040
A new day is upon us.

479
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,560
The hill myna in the birdhouse
has begun to whistle.

480
00:41:14,830 --> 00:41:16,280
That is not true.

481
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:18,890
There is an owl within.

482
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,320
It is still dark outside.

483
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,390
Better, is it not?

484
00:41:36,850 --> 00:41:38,730
You seemed very unwell last night.

485
00:41:39,830 --> 00:41:40,830
Well...

486
00:41:41,140 --> 00:41:42,640
I was thinking about Cherd.

487
00:41:49,420 --> 00:41:50,500
Last night,

488
00:41:51,950 --> 00:41:54,760
when his men bound me,

489
00:41:56,540 --> 00:41:59,270
Cherd sang me a lullaby.

490
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:00,350
It made me shiver.

491
00:42:01,710 --> 00:42:04,260
The lullaby had some meaning.

492
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:06,390
Wat Bot.

493
00:42:07,470 --> 00:42:08,730
Toddy palms.

494
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:11,180
Khun Thong.

495
00:42:12,240 --> 00:42:13,700
♫That Khun Thong had met♫

496
00:42:14,970 --> 00:42:16,300
♫His fate♫

497
00:42:20,270 --> 00:42:22,050
He must be yearning for his father.

498
00:42:23,660 --> 00:42:25,240
My men once told me that

499
00:42:26,260 --> 00:42:28,330
his father owned a toddy palm grove.

500
00:42:29,830 --> 00:42:32,850
It was said that he fell from a height,
leaving him broken.

501
00:42:46,570 --> 00:42:48,240
Cherd loved his father dearly.

502
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:50,320
After his father was crippled,

503
00:42:52,260 --> 00:42:54,330
Cherd's mother became a drunkard

504
00:42:57,160 --> 00:43:00,010
and began beating his father
out of exhaustion.

505
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:03,860
In the end, he perished,

506
00:43:06,580 --> 00:43:08,800
and she descended into madness.

507
00:43:10,170 --> 00:43:12,430
That is why Cherd took refuge in opium.

508
00:43:17,590 --> 00:43:19,050
He must have been in deep sorrow.

509
00:43:19,330 --> 00:43:22,050
He was often troubled by nightmares
of his mother murdering his father.

510
00:43:27,070 --> 00:43:28,370
He likely wishes...

511
00:43:28,730 --> 00:43:30,020
to sleep without dreams.

512
00:43:33,580 --> 00:43:36,400
That is why you do not wish me
to have a quarrel with him, is it not?

513
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:42,360
And that is why

514
00:43:43,420 --> 00:43:46,150
Lord Harn gave Cherd opium,
thereby turning him into an addict.

515
00:43:46,930 --> 00:43:48,630
This would allow Cherd
to be used as his tool.

516
00:43:50,270 --> 00:43:51,130
And Cherd...

517
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:53,570
loves Lord Harn,
treating him as his new father.

518
00:43:55,780 --> 00:43:57,560
The reason he was charmed by Pim

519
00:43:58,190 --> 00:43:59,040
was...

520
00:43:59,340 --> 00:44:01,890
the lack of love given by a woman

521
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:03,440
such as his own mother.

522
00:44:04,900 --> 00:44:06,000
Even Cherd

523
00:44:07,140 --> 00:44:09,720
is not a demon from hell as we thought,

524
00:44:11,030 --> 00:44:12,920
but someone has made him so.

525
00:44:17,720 --> 00:44:18,990
My dearest.

526
00:44:20,630 --> 00:44:22,960
You truly have a sympathetic heart,

527
00:44:25,420 --> 00:44:27,430
despite his having hurt you so much.

528
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:33,070
I understood him,

529
00:44:33,340 --> 00:44:34,660
but I do not stand by his side.

530
00:44:35,690 --> 00:44:38,280
And karma has caught up with him.

531
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:47,360
At last,

532
00:44:48,410 --> 00:44:50,780
Klao had once again been slain,

533
00:44:52,570 --> 00:44:55,600
despite my having already killed him
with my own hands.

534
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:11,720
What ails you, Phop?

535
00:45:15,790 --> 00:45:17,080
I have something to inquire of you.

536
00:45:19,320 --> 00:45:21,520
Did he learn something from Lord Harn?

537
00:45:22,370 --> 00:45:24,070
Should I tell him now

538
00:45:24,260 --> 00:45:25,500
that I am from the future?

539
00:45:26,440 --> 00:45:29,840
No one knows
when I'll be brought back either.

540
00:45:37,970 --> 00:45:39,640
The temple holds
a merit-making ceremony tonight.

541
00:45:40,610 --> 00:45:41,960
Would you like to join me?

542
00:45:51,350 --> 00:45:53,160
That said, let us go and wash ourselves.

543
00:46:14,050 --> 00:46:15,000
It's fine.

544
00:46:16,060 --> 00:46:17,280
Focus on the present moment.

545
00:46:17,940 --> 00:46:19,720
Cherd has been arrested.

546
00:46:20,200 --> 00:46:22,120
It is best to enjoy my time with Phop,

547
00:46:23,060 --> 00:46:24,600
one moment at a time.

548
00:46:56,820 --> 00:46:58,530
Cherd's whereabouts remain unknown.

549
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:01,610
The firearm taken from the Farangi
has also disappeared.

550
00:47:02,290 --> 00:47:03,600
Inform Lord Phop at once!

551
00:47:03,870 --> 00:47:05,880
He and Master Klao are in grave danger!!

552
00:49:05,560 --> 00:49:07,240
Your prayers were rather extensive, Phop.

553
00:49:10,280 --> 00:49:12,000
Will the Buddha take heed of all that?

554
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:17,720
I call upon the Buddha as my witness:

555
00:49:18,730 --> 00:49:21,330
my heart belongs to you alone,
and ever shall it remain.

556
00:49:24,420 --> 00:49:26,600
I shall approach my parents

557
00:49:28,380 --> 00:49:29,920
to ask for your hand in marriage.

558
00:49:35,360 --> 00:49:38,480
Then I shall cherish
and protect the very heart of my life

559
00:49:39,590 --> 00:49:40,960
until the end of my days.

560
00:49:45,250 --> 00:49:46,800
This is another wish of mine.

561
00:49:49,330 --> 00:49:51,180
Should there be another lifetime,

562
00:49:52,060 --> 00:49:54,200
we shall seek each other out once more.

563
00:49:57,320 --> 00:49:59,080
May our love remain steadfast,

564
00:50:00,440 --> 00:50:02,320
though the tides of time may turn.

565
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:08,400
But...

566
00:50:10,110 --> 00:50:11,640
After this day,

567
00:50:12,430 --> 00:50:13,890
if I am gone,

568
00:50:17,460 --> 00:50:19,240
promise me you will live well.

569
00:50:20,830 --> 00:50:21,720
No.

570
00:50:35,340 --> 00:50:37,320
I shall seek you out...

571
00:50:38,230 --> 00:50:39,560
until I find you

572
00:50:41,650 --> 00:50:43,360
and love you once more.

573
00:51:22,270 --> 00:51:23,800
Do you remember that shop still?

574
00:51:25,140 --> 00:51:27,340
We should choose new rings together.

575
00:51:32,430 --> 00:51:33,830
This one is my very favorite.

576
00:51:36,060 --> 00:51:37,060
Good heavens!

577
00:51:37,420 --> 00:51:39,750
I must have taken it off
when I bathed.

578
00:51:40,280 --> 00:51:41,720
I forgot to put it back on.

579
00:51:43,400 --> 00:51:44,760
Think no more of it.

580
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:47,360
We shall procure a finer ring than the last.

581
00:51:48,240 --> 00:51:49,720
Which kind do you prefer?

582
00:51:49,930 --> 00:51:51,540
I shall engrave it upon my heart

583
00:51:53,180 --> 00:51:56,080
for when the time comes
to acquire your wedding ring.

584
00:52:21,620 --> 00:52:22,260
Cherd!

585
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:23,240
How came he here?!

586
00:52:23,550 --> 00:52:24,280
Run! Now!

587
00:52:29,170 --> 00:52:30,170
Make way! Make way!

588
00:52:45,410 --> 00:52:46,880
We can go no further.

589
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:49,320
You must hide here.

590
00:52:50,160 --> 00:52:51,320
I shall go and seize him myself.

591
00:52:52,360 --> 00:52:53,700
No, I beg you!

592
00:52:54,730 --> 00:52:56,160
What if we should be parted again?

593
00:52:56,900 --> 00:52:58,410
Countless times have we been parted,

594
00:52:58,970 --> 00:53:00,820
yet ever do I find my way to you.

595
00:53:05,940 --> 00:53:07,110
I promise you,

596
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:10,120
I shall return.

597
00:53:11,470 --> 00:53:13,560
Nothing shall ever part us again.

598
00:53:21,770 --> 00:53:23,520
Klao!!

599
00:53:27,810 --> 00:53:29,640
You shall never escape my grasp!

600
00:53:31,420 --> 00:53:33,200
Your sins are already
too great to bear, Cherd!

601
00:53:34,520 --> 00:53:35,740
I beg of you, let me go.

602
00:53:36,870 --> 00:53:37,760
Hear me well,

603
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:39,600
or you shall be sentenced to death.

604
00:53:39,660 --> 00:53:40,920
I care not!!

605
00:53:42,930 --> 00:53:46,160
You must die by my hand alone!

606
00:53:46,420 --> 00:53:47,310
Lower the firearm!

607
00:53:48,280 --> 00:53:49,040
Cease this!

608
00:53:49,570 --> 00:53:50,350
Or else,

609
00:53:50,710 --> 00:53:52,680
you shall be sent to the depths of hell
this very instant!

610
00:53:54,670 --> 00:53:56,310
Should I be sent there,

611
00:53:58,760 --> 00:54:00,440
then I shall drag you down with me!!

612
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:52,800
I shall seek you out...

613
00:54:53,810 --> 00:54:55,420
until I find you

614
00:54:57,260 --> 00:54:58,950
and love you once more.

615
00:55:00,250 --> 00:55:01,320
Phop!

616
00:55:10,690 --> 00:55:12,080
Phop, where are you?

617
00:55:14,820 --> 00:55:15,750
Phop.

618
00:55:37,620 --> 00:55:38,800
I'm back home?

619
00:56:22,310 --> 00:56:23,000
Nakun!

620
00:56:24,410 --> 00:56:25,300
Nakun, my dear!

621
00:56:27,130 --> 00:56:27,720
Nakun!!

622
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:29,230
That way.

623
00:56:29,410 --> 00:56:30,200
That way!

624
00:56:30,710 --> 00:56:31,340
Mom...

625
00:56:32,700 --> 00:56:33,440
Is that you?

626
00:56:41,210 --> 00:56:41,850
He has come to.

627
00:56:41,890 --> 00:56:43,560
Hey, can you hear me?

628
00:56:43,610 --> 00:56:45,220
If you do, please blink.

629
00:56:45,970 --> 00:56:47,560
Are you injured in any way?

630
00:56:49,850 --> 00:56:50,720
Nakun.

631
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:53,240
Sweetie!!

632
00:56:54,720 --> 00:56:55,720
My dear.

633
00:56:56,450 --> 00:56:57,160
Nakun.

634
00:57:05,100 --> 00:57:05,980
Mom.

635
00:57:07,470 --> 00:57:08,800
Is this really you?

636
00:57:11,770 --> 00:57:13,760
Of course, it's me.

637
00:57:14,570 --> 00:57:15,400
Nakun...

638
00:57:16,900 --> 00:57:17,850
What's the matter?

639
00:57:17,970 --> 00:57:19,680
What's wrong? Are you hurt?

640
00:57:19,960 --> 00:57:21,080
Tell me where it hurts.

641
00:57:24,110 --> 00:57:26,440
Please take me to Phop, Mom.

642
00:57:35,380 --> 00:57:38,220
Mom, please take me to Phop.

643
00:57:38,520 --> 00:57:39,290
My dear...

644
00:57:58,740 --> 00:58:01,010
Seeing you healthy is all I could ask for.

645
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:04,050
The doctor told you to rest a lot.

646
00:58:04,740 --> 00:58:07,210
Get some rest, okay?

647
00:58:13,340 --> 00:58:14,340
Dear.

648
00:58:17,850 --> 00:58:19,440
Is something wrong?

649
00:58:20,330 --> 00:58:22,200
Tell me if anything is bothering you.

650
00:58:25,110 --> 00:58:26,050
Dear...

651
00:58:28,540 --> 00:58:31,100
what were you doing
at the orchard all night?

652
00:58:40,980 --> 00:58:42,550
All night?

653
00:58:44,120 --> 00:58:45,360
Yes, you heard me.

654
00:58:45,390 --> 00:58:47,290
You even got yourself a bottle of alcohol.

655
00:58:48,090 --> 00:58:48,980
Nakun...

656
00:58:51,420 --> 00:58:53,930
You can tell me
what's stressing you out, okay?

657
00:58:58,390 --> 00:58:59,390
How...

658
00:59:00,220 --> 00:59:02,440
long was I out?

659
00:59:05,160 --> 00:59:06,700
I don't really know either.

660
00:59:07,210 --> 00:59:10,810
It was well past 11 P.M.
when I came back from the wedding.

661
00:59:11,100 --> 00:59:13,040
You were already gone when I got home.

662
00:59:13,520 --> 00:59:14,590
And I thought

663
00:59:14,950 --> 00:59:16,960
you went to get something around here.

664
00:59:17,920 --> 00:59:19,730
I waited for so long,

665
00:59:19,950 --> 00:59:21,680
but you still hadn't come back.

666
00:59:22,780 --> 00:59:25,520
You didn't bring your phone with you either.

667
00:59:26,530 --> 00:59:27,530
I thought

668
00:59:28,210 --> 00:59:31,000
things were starting to feel a bit off.

669
00:59:31,730 --> 00:59:34,340
Then I saw you lying there in the orchard...

670
00:59:34,610 --> 00:59:36,730
And you were wearing some very odd clothes.

671
00:59:39,920 --> 00:59:42,520
I tried so hard to wake you up, but...

672
00:59:43,340 --> 00:59:44,800
you wouldn't open your eyes.

673
00:59:45,800 --> 00:59:47,160
I was so horrified...

674
00:59:47,820 --> 00:59:50,140
that I called emergency services.

675
00:59:50,290 --> 00:59:50,720
And...

676
00:59:51,660 --> 00:59:53,280
less than an hour later,

677
00:59:54,260 --> 00:59:55,790
you woke up.

678
01:00:00,380 --> 01:00:01,720
Less than an hour?

679
01:00:02,770 --> 01:00:03,550
Nakun.

680
01:00:05,560 --> 01:00:06,960
It had been less than an hour,

681
01:00:07,420 --> 01:00:10,040
but my heart almost couldn't take it.

682
01:00:12,780 --> 01:00:15,480
I was terrified something bad
had happened to you.

683
01:00:49,280 --> 01:00:50,560
The professor said that

684
01:00:51,530 --> 01:00:52,950
upon completing the mission,

685
01:00:54,010 --> 01:00:55,720
the character
would be able to return to their world.

686
01:00:56,460 --> 01:00:56,920
However...

687
01:00:58,270 --> 01:01:02,300
should the main character
fail their mission,

688
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:06,470
the portal would be closed forever,

689
01:01:06,500 --> 01:01:10,000
preventing their return to their world.

690
01:01:11,520 --> 01:01:12,410
That's a lie.

691
01:01:13,350 --> 01:01:15,670
Even though we knew who the culprit was,

692
01:01:16,820 --> 01:01:18,520
Cherd managed to escape.

693
01:01:19,820 --> 01:01:21,640
Harn is also still at large.

694
01:01:22,870 --> 01:01:24,830
How can my mission be considered complete?

695
01:01:25,720 --> 01:01:29,440
If you can't manage a full meal,
at least have some fruit.

696
01:01:58,680 --> 01:02:00,640
It is of the finest quality,

697
01:02:01,150 --> 01:02:02,880
brought by traders from across China.

698
01:02:05,620 --> 01:02:06,620
Thanks.

699
01:02:07,750 --> 01:02:08,520
Phop.

700
01:02:09,830 --> 01:02:11,290
I wonder how you're doing.

701
01:02:14,680 --> 01:02:15,840
["Lord Phop"]

702
01:02:18,600 --> 01:02:19,860
[No results were found for
"Lord Phop" and "Patrol Department"]

703
01:02:19,890 --> 01:02:21,800
[No results were found for
"Lord Preechapiban"]

704
01:02:21,860 --> 01:02:23,720
[No results were found for
"High Lord Pichayabhakdi"]

705
01:02:24,450 --> 01:02:26,040
There is no information at all.

706
01:02:26,970 --> 01:02:29,440
Phop doesn't even exist in the history books.

707
01:02:31,300 --> 01:02:32,960
Or do I have to wait until the next starfall?

708
01:02:33,920 --> 01:02:35,860
Or do I have to wait until my next birthday?

709
01:02:42,650 --> 01:02:43,600
Phop.

710
01:02:45,370 --> 01:02:47,160
I shall find my way back to you.

711
01:03:15,450 --> 01:03:21,440
♫Where are you right now?♫

712
01:03:21,620 --> 01:03:27,740
♫Can you hear this heart crying out somehow?♫

713
01:03:27,790 --> 01:03:34,330
♫Do you know
there's someone waiting for you still?♫

714
01:03:34,420 --> 01:03:39,800
♫Every night I dream of you,
and always will♫

715
01:03:40,180 --> 01:03:46,120
♫Even time means nothing now♫

716
01:03:46,330 --> 01:03:51,490
♫No matter how long,
I'll wait for you somehow♫

717
01:03:51,530 --> 01:03:55,590
♫Though distance keeps our worlds apart♫

718
01:03:55,650 --> 01:03:58,310
♫It cannot separate our hearts♫

719
01:03:58,330 --> 01:04:03,590
♫Our love still travels through the dark♫

720
01:04:03,640 --> 01:04:07,560
♫If you were born to share my heart♫

721
01:04:07,590 --> 01:04:10,550
♫Like the moon beside the night♫

722
01:04:10,590 --> 01:04:16,810
♫I know someday our souls will reunite♫

723
01:04:17,040 --> 01:04:22,400
♫No matter how far we are apart,♫

724
01:04:23,230 --> 01:04:29,170
♫It will never be too far,
if our hearts stay strong♫

725
01:04:29,410 --> 01:04:35,600
♫Across all lifetimes,
nothing could keep us apart♫

726
01:04:35,620 --> 01:04:39,780
♫As long as our hearts remain as one,
where they belong♫

727
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:40,720
[Chances of seeing shooting stars in Ayutthaya]

728
01:04:41,650 --> 01:04:44,080
♫As long as our hearts remain as one♫

729
01:04:44,120 --> 01:04:46,060
[Shooting stars can appear
any month, all year round, Nakun]

730
01:04:46,080 --> 01:04:47,650
[In fact, it can be seen
one to three times a month]

731
01:04:47,670 --> 01:04:49,360
[You can see it
depending on how clear the sky is]

732
01:04:53,330 --> 01:04:55,280
Your mom said
you're feeling a bit dazed, right?

733
01:04:55,500 --> 01:04:57,190
That's why I brought you some vitamins.

734
01:05:04,420 --> 01:05:05,220
Jom!

735
01:05:12,390 --> 01:05:13,030
Jom...

736
01:05:15,540 --> 01:05:16,480
Who the hell is Jom?

737
01:05:17,720 --> 01:05:19,700
You miss me that much, don't you?

738
01:05:20,340 --> 01:05:21,200
I'm touched.

739
01:05:26,030 --> 01:05:26,730
You...

740
01:05:27,360 --> 01:05:28,300
You don't remember it?

741
01:05:29,650 --> 01:05:30,520
Remember what?

742
01:05:30,940 --> 01:05:33,050
You're the one who doesn't remember me.

743
01:05:33,720 --> 01:05:34,720
You...

744
01:05:35,460 --> 01:05:36,490
You have amnesia?

745
01:05:50,920 --> 01:05:53,120
Jom was probably Thee in a past life.

746
01:05:54,860 --> 01:05:56,760
Thee didn't travel through time like I did.

747
01:05:59,350 --> 01:06:00,800
Your mom is really worried about you.

748
01:06:01,660 --> 01:06:02,800
You refuse to leave your room,

749
01:06:03,140 --> 01:06:03,800
and at night,

750
01:06:04,210 --> 01:06:06,080
you stay on the balcony until dawn.

751
01:06:06,430 --> 01:06:08,320
If you can't tell her, tell me instead.

752
01:06:11,070 --> 01:06:12,300
What's wrong?

753
01:06:18,230 --> 01:06:20,000
Alright. It's fine
if you don't want to tell me.

754
01:06:21,170 --> 01:06:23,200
But you've been absent
from your classes for almost a week now.

755
01:06:24,780 --> 01:06:25,840
Wanna go back to university?

756
01:06:26,580 --> 01:06:27,580
Be with Pun

757
01:06:28,220 --> 01:06:29,120
and me.

758
01:06:30,240 --> 01:06:32,320
Maybe we can help you feel better.

759
01:06:36,420 --> 01:06:38,050
Pun is really worried about you, you know?

760
01:06:38,680 --> 01:06:40,360
He's sad because he's worried about you.

761
01:06:41,030 --> 01:06:42,260
That's why I'm sad too.

762
01:06:43,270 --> 01:06:43,940
Just look.

763
01:06:44,730 --> 01:06:45,730
I'm trying to smile,

764
01:06:46,780 --> 01:06:47,930
but I just can't.

765
01:06:51,560 --> 01:06:52,230
See?

766
01:06:54,820 --> 01:06:55,940
Come to the university, please.

767
01:07:08,140 --> 01:07:08,880
Nakun.

768
01:07:10,810 --> 01:07:11,640
Nakun!

769
01:07:14,950 --> 01:07:16,010
Eat up, will you?

770
01:07:17,770 --> 01:07:19,040
We have classes all afternoon.

771
01:07:20,270 --> 01:07:21,080
Sorry.

772
01:07:21,660 --> 01:07:23,600
I was lost in my thoughts
and had too much fun.

773
01:07:25,920 --> 01:07:26,520
But...

774
01:07:26,710 --> 01:07:28,560
it didn't seem like
you were having much fun at all.

775
01:07:32,480 --> 01:07:33,720
Yeah, he's right.

776
01:07:34,220 --> 01:07:35,840
Let us know
if there's something on your mind.

777
01:07:35,970 --> 01:07:37,000
Just tell us.

778
01:07:37,440 --> 01:07:39,640
We listen; we don't judge.

779
01:07:40,730 --> 01:07:41,800
Thee.

780
01:07:42,430 --> 01:07:43,430
This isn't the time.

781
01:07:45,860 --> 01:07:46,930
Nakun,

782
01:07:47,650 --> 01:07:48,650
are you alright?

783
01:07:49,920 --> 01:07:51,600
Do you want to take the afternoon off?

784
01:07:56,990 --> 01:07:57,720
Thee.

785
01:07:58,120 --> 01:08:00,010
Should we take him back to his place?

786
01:08:00,440 --> 01:08:01,200
Mhm.

787
01:08:05,030 --> 01:08:05,900
It's fine.

788
01:08:06,310 --> 01:08:07,400
Seriously?

789
01:08:08,180 --> 01:08:10,200
You've been zoning out all day.

790
01:08:11,190 --> 01:08:13,840
Have your misfortunes been upsetting you?

791
01:08:14,580 --> 01:08:18,080
Did you do what the fortune teller said
when you returned home?

792
01:08:20,390 --> 01:08:21,319
Guys...

793
01:08:23,260 --> 01:08:25,479
Can you take me to see
the fortune teller again?

794
01:08:28,010 --> 01:08:28,920
The fortune teller...

795
01:08:34,060 --> 01:08:36,420
Fortune teller, do you remember me?

796
01:08:39,200 --> 01:08:40,189
Indeed, I do.

797
01:08:41,819 --> 01:08:42,950
You came to see me the other day.

798
01:08:45,060 --> 01:08:45,970
No.

799
01:08:49,210 --> 01:08:50,080
What should we have tomorrow?

800
01:08:50,420 --> 01:08:53,040
- Anything works for me.
- Oh.

801
01:08:55,330 --> 01:08:56,160
Uh...

802
01:08:57,069 --> 01:08:59,000
It's... It's Klao.

803
01:08:59,399 --> 01:09:00,319
Remember?

804
01:09:02,130 --> 01:09:03,479
My hair looks like a cow's?

805
01:09:06,779 --> 01:09:08,279
It looks fine to me.

806
01:09:09,430 --> 01:09:10,479
It's flowing.

807
01:09:10,720 --> 01:09:11,540
Fortune teller.

808
01:09:11,649 --> 01:09:12,450
I'm serious.

809
01:09:16,040 --> 01:09:16,920
I'm Klao,

810
01:09:17,319 --> 01:09:19,529
a resident of Lord Phop's manor.

811
01:09:20,500 --> 01:09:21,600
Lady Prayong is his mother.

812
01:09:22,279 --> 01:09:23,220
She's the lady who...

813
01:09:23,600 --> 01:09:25,359
often gives you money.

814
01:09:26,580 --> 01:09:27,420
Uh...

815
01:09:28,210 --> 01:09:29,210
Uh, I do remember.

816
01:09:30,090 --> 01:09:30,850
Klao.

817
01:09:32,080 --> 01:09:32,819
I remember.

818
01:09:32,910 --> 01:09:34,080
You remember me now, don't you?

819
01:09:35,600 --> 01:09:36,840
If you do,

820
01:09:37,240 --> 01:09:38,760
could you tell me how Phop is doing?

821
01:09:41,310 --> 01:09:42,640
Now that I've returned here,

822
01:09:43,100 --> 01:09:44,399
is he still safe?

823
01:09:45,420 --> 01:09:46,279
I beg you.

824
01:09:46,609 --> 01:09:47,740
Please tell me.

825
01:09:47,830 --> 01:09:49,050
I can't take it anymore.

826
01:09:51,080 --> 01:09:52,080
If you want to know,

827
01:09:53,359 --> 01:09:54,400
I need to read your cards.

828
01:09:58,560 --> 01:09:59,440
Read my cards...

829
01:09:59,870 --> 01:10:00,860
For what?

830
01:10:01,740 --> 01:10:04,240
If you remember our past life,

831
01:10:04,880 --> 01:10:06,680
you must know how Phop is doing right now.

832
01:10:29,540 --> 01:10:30,660
"Loss."

833
01:10:31,770 --> 01:10:33,040
"Separation."

834
01:10:34,880 --> 01:10:36,300
"A deep fear of change."

835
01:10:38,030 --> 01:10:38,850
Phop...

836
01:10:39,830 --> 01:10:41,030
The person you're thinking of

837
01:10:44,400 --> 01:10:45,610
has met his fate.

838
01:11:00,090 --> 01:11:01,080
That's not true!!

839
01:11:01,210 --> 01:11:01,830
Nakun.

840
01:11:01,860 --> 01:11:03,080
Nakun, Nakun.

841
01:11:03,230 --> 01:11:03,940
Nakun.

842
01:11:04,560 --> 01:11:05,240
Nakun...

843
01:11:05,870 --> 01:11:06,820
Let me go!

844
01:11:13,650 --> 01:11:14,340
The stone.

845
01:11:14,480 --> 01:11:15,280
That stone.

846
01:11:17,010 --> 01:11:18,220
So you also...

847
01:11:18,260 --> 01:11:19,640
traveled back in time like I did?

848
01:11:22,110 --> 01:11:23,420
Nakun, enough.

849
01:11:24,020 --> 01:11:25,020
Did you?

850
01:11:26,590 --> 01:11:27,360
Let go!

851
01:11:27,460 --> 01:11:28,560
I told you to let go.

852
01:11:28,790 --> 01:11:29,880
Let go of me.

853
01:11:30,270 --> 01:11:31,280
Let go of me!!

854
01:11:32,160 --> 01:11:33,890
Please, let go of me.

855
01:11:45,240 --> 01:11:46,390
Fortune teller.

856
01:11:49,610 --> 01:11:50,810
I beg you.

857
01:11:52,320 --> 01:11:53,190
Please...

858
01:11:53,520 --> 01:11:54,340
Can you...

859
01:11:54,880 --> 01:11:56,350
try to remember

860
01:11:57,320 --> 01:12:00,360
what happened to Phop? Is he still safe?

861
01:12:02,030 --> 01:12:03,760
If you really don't know,

862
01:12:05,550 --> 01:12:08,850
can you tell me
how I could travel back in time to Ayothaya?

863
01:12:10,270 --> 01:12:11,140
In your past life,

864
01:12:11,930 --> 01:12:14,250
you helped me so much.

865
01:12:16,070 --> 01:12:17,920
You were extraordinary!

866
01:12:19,320 --> 01:12:21,780
Why must you act so clueless in this life?!!

867
01:12:37,200 --> 01:12:38,080
Yes.

868
01:12:40,230 --> 01:12:42,410
I was better in my past life.

869
01:12:42,990 --> 01:12:45,480
To let go of the old is to welcome the new.

870
01:12:48,640 --> 01:12:51,050
A great change is upon us;

871
01:12:51,820 --> 01:12:53,440
an ending that gives birth
to a new beginning.

872
01:12:53,940 --> 01:12:55,790
Lord Phop has met his end,

873
01:12:56,240 --> 01:12:57,960
yet he shall return once more.

874
01:13:07,880 --> 01:13:09,900
Even the fortune teller is no help.

875
01:13:11,450 --> 01:13:13,120
I guess I have to let it go.

876
01:13:19,360 --> 01:13:22,170
Our amuse-bouche
comes in the form of traditional Thai dishes

877
01:13:22,380 --> 01:13:23,670
with a modern twist.

878
01:13:25,020 --> 01:13:26,240
Please enjoy your meal.

879
01:13:27,420 --> 01:13:28,200
Sai!

880
01:13:28,560 --> 01:13:29,230
Yes?

881
01:13:30,420 --> 01:13:30,770
Uh...

882
01:13:30,790 --> 01:13:32,460
I'm really sorry, sir.

883
01:13:32,610 --> 01:13:35,160
We're sorry for the delay
in serving your food.

884
01:13:35,750 --> 01:13:36,310
Uh...

885
01:13:36,940 --> 01:13:37,840
Not what I meant.

886
01:13:38,280 --> 01:13:39,040
Oh.

887
01:13:39,650 --> 01:13:40,650
I'm so sorry.

888
01:13:41,120 --> 01:13:42,480
I thought you were someone else.

889
01:13:43,840 --> 01:13:44,740
Right.

890
01:13:52,520 --> 01:13:53,560
Thee.

891
01:13:53,860 --> 01:13:54,880
See?

892
01:13:55,020 --> 01:13:57,600
I told you to just get him a room here.

893
01:13:58,020 --> 01:13:59,440
Yet, you brought him to the rooftop.

894
01:13:59,830 --> 01:14:01,040
I'm sorry.

895
01:14:01,740 --> 01:14:02,740
I thought...

896
01:14:02,790 --> 01:14:04,720
if he could enjoy good food

897
01:14:05,040 --> 01:14:06,550
with a scenic view,

898
01:14:07,220 --> 01:14:08,490
he might feel better.

899
01:14:14,440 --> 01:14:15,030
Hey,

900
01:14:15,490 --> 01:14:16,490
Pun.

901
01:14:17,460 --> 01:14:18,900
Since when did you become close to Thee?

902
01:14:22,590 --> 01:14:23,590
Well...

903
01:14:23,850 --> 01:14:25,020
Since...

904
01:14:25,470 --> 01:14:27,080
you were absent.

905
01:14:27,730 --> 01:14:29,990
After opening up to each other,

906
01:14:30,410 --> 01:14:33,610
I realized that he does have a soft side,

907
01:14:33,920 --> 01:14:35,810
beyond his constant joking.

908
01:14:42,220 --> 01:14:43,610
My actions from my past life

909
01:14:44,030 --> 01:14:45,800
really do affect the present day.

910
01:14:49,780 --> 01:14:52,590
So, would revealing
the truth about Klao's father

911
01:14:53,270 --> 01:14:55,000
have the same effect?

912
01:14:59,060 --> 01:15:00,100
If Sai...

913
01:15:00,690 --> 01:15:01,430
Jom...

914
01:15:01,950 --> 01:15:02,660
Kaew...

915
01:15:03,200 --> 01:15:04,130
The oracle...

916
01:15:05,090 --> 01:15:07,030
If they can reincarnate into this life,

917
01:15:07,660 --> 01:15:10,130
others might be able to as well.

918
01:15:11,230 --> 01:15:12,230
What about Phop?

919
01:15:13,300 --> 01:15:15,290
Did he reincarnate?

920
01:15:16,120 --> 01:15:17,620
Will he be able to remember me?

921
01:15:22,250 --> 01:15:23,040
Nakun.

922
01:15:23,630 --> 01:15:24,600
Are you okay?

923
01:15:28,010 --> 01:15:28,840
I'm not.

924
01:15:31,460 --> 01:15:32,680
I'm sorry, Thee.

925
01:15:34,340 --> 01:15:36,680
Pun, please finish the dishes for me.

926
01:15:41,110 --> 01:15:41,960
Nakun.

927
01:15:47,750 --> 01:15:49,110
Don't force him.

928
01:15:49,600 --> 01:15:51,560
- But...
- But what?

929
01:15:52,010 --> 01:15:54,140
His feelings come first.

930
01:16:47,160 --> 01:16:50,900
[Thee: Almost here, or another day?]

931
01:16:50,920 --> 01:16:54,920
[I'm here]

932
01:17:11,780 --> 01:17:13,540
I shall seek you out...

933
01:17:13,910 --> 01:17:15,080
until I find you

934
01:17:15,440 --> 01:17:16,930
and love you once more.

935
01:17:33,720 --> 01:17:35,080
In just a few weeks,

936
01:17:35,120 --> 01:17:36,640
my life has changed a lot.

937
01:17:36,660 --> 01:17:37,160
Let me help you.

938
01:17:37,190 --> 01:17:40,070
And in this new life
I'm trying to get used to,

939
01:17:40,120 --> 01:17:42,460
I've met familiar faces from my past life.

940
01:17:42,480 --> 01:17:43,640
A-Chai? Who?

941
01:17:44,900 --> 01:17:46,640
You! Are you alright?

942
01:17:46,710 --> 01:17:48,400
When you called me,

943
01:17:48,470 --> 01:17:49,760
I thought you already knew me.

944
01:17:49,790 --> 01:17:52,160
No. I was calling 'you' as a pronoun.

945
01:17:53,330 --> 01:17:54,900
Since Nakun left for Ayutthaya,

946
01:17:54,940 --> 01:17:56,680
I've only been dreaming of these things.

947
01:17:56,960 --> 01:17:59,080
It feels like I once fell for you, Thee.

948
01:17:59,510 --> 01:18:00,720
But you...

949
01:18:01,160 --> 01:18:02,930
You kept rejecting me.

950
01:18:03,000 --> 01:18:04,760
[Can you help me get back to Ayutthaya?]

951
01:18:05,550 --> 01:18:06,960
Let's take in the scenery
from the top of the prang.

952
01:18:07,180 --> 01:18:09,220
Its condition remains
as pristine as it was back then.

953
01:18:10,030 --> 01:18:10,730
You...

954
01:18:11,070 --> 01:18:12,830
Your memories have always been there, right?

955
01:18:13,310 --> 01:18:17,490
♫Though distance keeps our worlds apart♫

956
01:18:17,520 --> 01:18:20,140
♫It cannot separate our hearts♫

957
01:18:20,190 --> 01:18:25,430
♫Our love still travels through the dark♫

958
01:18:25,460 --> 01:18:29,300
♫If you were born to share my heart♫

959
01:18:29,330 --> 01:18:32,360
♫Like the moon beside the night♫

960
01:18:32,390 --> 01:18:38,720
♫I know someday our souls will reunite♫

961
01:18:38,870 --> 01:18:44,360
♫No matter how far we are apart,♫

962
01:18:45,080 --> 01:18:51,150
♫It will never be too far,
if our hearts stay strong♫

963
01:18:51,190 --> 01:18:57,390
♫Across all lifetimes,
nothing could keep us apart♫

964
01:18:57,480 --> 01:19:03,370
♫As long as our hearts remain as one,
where they belong♫

965
01:19:03,550 --> 01:19:09,360
♫As long as our hearts remain as one,
where they belong♫

966
01:19:09,380 --> 01:19:13,100
[Love Upon a Time Series]

